706543f-a.text:
Ryder Ave., at the S.W. corner of Ave. S., sho ing the home of E.H. Ryder from 1860-1873. E. Ryder was owner in 1857, and in 1922 one
Hill was the occupant.
April 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
706543f-a.folder: Ryder Avenue & Avenue S, Brooklyn, NY

706542f-b.text:
(1)
Ryder ave., at the S.W. corner of Ave. S., showing the hone of E. Ryder (1857) and E.H. Ryder (1860-1873). It was occupied by one Hill in 1922. This houee.in the Brooklyn Atlas of 1929,is in East 29th Street, just south of Ave. S., and will either be moved or demolished at
a subsequent date.
1922.
Eugene L. Am4uruster Collection.
(2)
The same, looking north on Ryder Ave.
April 1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(3)
The same, showing the barns near East 28th Street.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
